Los Angeles has been chosen to host the Olympic and Paralympic Games in 2028, marking the return of the Olympics to the United States. The United States Olympic Committee and the bid team were commended for their plan to showcase American creativity, innovation, and hospitality. The United States has a strong history of supporting the Olympic Movement, with the most Olympic medals and trained athletes. The Games are seen as a celebration of humanity and hold a special place in the hearts of Americans. The Summer Games in Los Angeles are expected to embody the Olympic ideal and the American spirit.